These are Puzzles for 1x7 Level 4

.:: Puzzle 1x7-Level-4-1::.
The people's birthday is in 7 different months: august, january, june, may, september, october, july
1. the person who's birthday is in september is between the person who's birthday is in june and the person who's birthday is in january##2
2. the person who's birthday is in october is on the right of the person who's birthday is in august##1
3. the person who's birthday is in july is on the right of the person who's birthday is in may##1
4. the person who's birthday is in october is in the middle##1
5. the person who's birthday is in january is in an odd position##4
6. the person who's birthday is in june is on the left of the person who's birthday is in september##1
7. the person who's birthday is in august is in an odd position##4

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1    |    2    |     3     |    4    |   5    |    6     |    7     |
| Birthday   | may | july | august | october | june | september | january |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x7-Level-4-2::.
There are 7 different nationalities: french, indian, japanese, mexican, german, colombian, nigerian
1. the mexican is on the left of the japanese##1
2. the german is on the far left##1
3. the indian is on the right of the colombian##1
4. the japanese is in an even position##4
5. the german is on the left of the french##1
6. the colombian is on the left or right of the french##3

.:: Answer ::.
|         |      1       |     2     |   3    |    4     |    5    |  6   |     7      |
| Nationality   | german | french | colombian | indian | mexican | japanese | nigerian |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x7-Level-4-3::.
7 different games are played: scrabble, snooker, billiard, chess, bridge, canasta, whist
1. the person playing billiard is on the right of the person playing whist##1
2. the person playing scrabble is on the left of the person playing bridge##1
3. the person playing snooker is on the left or right of the person playing chess##3
4. the person playing bridge is on the left or right of the person playing whist##3
5. the person playing chess is on the left of the person playing scrabble##1
6. the person playing scrabble is on the left of the person playing bridge##1
7. the person playing billiard is in an even position##4
8. the person playing scrabble is on the left of the person playing bridge##1

.:: Answer ::.
|       |    1     |   2   |      3      |         4          |      5       |     6     |    7    |
| Game   | snooker | chess | scrabble | bridge | whist | billiard | canasta |

